						<summary>

						<p>This is mutilated at the right end. It records a gift of sheep for a perpetual lamp in the temple (Tirumuttirukkōyil) at Śēṟṟūr a <hi rend="italic">dēvadāna</hi> in Śēṟṟūr-kūṟṟam by a resident of Kīramaṅgalam in Poyyil-kūṟṟam. The early writing seems to point to the reign of <hi rend="bold">Parāntaka I</hi> for this record.</p>						

						</summary>
